.TH TODAY 1 "December 2025" "today 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
today \- A unified productivity dashboard for your terminal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B today
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B today
is a terminal-based productivity application that combines tasks, habits, and time tracking in a single, keyboard-driven interface. All data is stored locally as plain JSON files.
.PP
The application provides three main panes:
.IP \(bu 2
\fBTasks\fR: Manage your to-do list with vim-style navigation
.IP \(bu 2
\fBTimer\fR: Track time spent on projects with daily and weekly summaries
.IP \(bu 2
\fBHabits\fR: Track daily habits with visual week view and streak counting
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message and exit
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Display version information and exit
.SH KEYBINDINGS
.SS Global Keybindings
.TP
.B Tab
Switch to the next pane (Tasks \(-> Timer \(-> Habits \(-> Tasks)
.TP
.B 1
Jump directly to the Tasks pane
.TP
.B 2
Jump directly to the Timer pane
.TP
.B 3
Jump directly to the Habits pane
.TP
.B ?
Show help overlay with all keybindings
.TP
.B q
Quit the application
.SS Tasks Pane
.TP
.BR j ", " Down
Move selection down
.TP
.BR k ", " Up
Move selection up
.TP
.B a
Add a new task (enters input mode)
.TP
.BR d ", " Space ", " Enter
Toggle the selected task's completion status
.TP
.B x
Delete the selected task
.TP
.B g
Jump to the first task
.TP
.B G
Jump to the last task
.SS Timer Pane
.TP
.BR Space ", " Enter
Start or stop the current timer
.TP
.B s
Switch to a different project (prompts for project name and starts new timer)
.TP
.B x
Stop the current timer
.SS Habits Pane
.TP
.BR j ", " Down
Move selection down
.TP
.BR k ", " Up
Move selection up
.TP
.B a
Add a new habit (prompts for name, then icon)
.TP
.BR d ", " Space ", " Enter
Toggle today's completion for the selected habit
.TP
.B x
Delete the selected habit
.SS Input Mode
When adding tasks or habits, the following keys are available:
.TP
.B Enter
Save the input and return to normal mode
.TP
.B Esc
Cancel the input and return to normal mode without saving
.SH DATA STORAGE
All data is stored in the user's home directory under
.IR ~/.today/ :
.TP
.I ~/.today/tasks.json
Task list with completion status
.TP
.I ~/.today/habits.json
Habit definitions and completion logs
.TP
.I ~/.today/timer.json
Time tracking entries with project names and timestamps
.PP
All files are plain JSON and can be backed up, version controlled with git, or edited manually if needed.
.SH CONFIGURATION
An optional configuration file can be placed at:
.PP
.I ~/.config/today/config.yaml
.PP
The configuration file supports the following options:
.TP
.B data_dir
Override the default data directory (default: ~/.today)
.PP
Example configuration:
.PP
.nf
.RS
data_dir: ~/Documents/today-data
.RE
.fi
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Start the application:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ today
.RE
.fi
.TP
Show version information:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ today --version
.RE
.fi
.TP
Display help:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ today --help
.RE
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.today/tasks.json
Tasks database
.TP
.I ~/.today/habits.json
Habits database
.TP
.I ~/.today/timer.json
Timer entries database
.TP
.I ~/.config/today/config.yaml
Optional configuration file
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.B today
respects standard terminal environment variables:
.TP
.B TERM
Terminal type, should support colors for best experience
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
If set, disables colored output
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Error occurred (config error, storage error, or runtime error)
